inn1.comm: that was friendly. Guptill should really have said a word of thanks to Irfan as he punches a loose full toss on off stump down the ground to the long-off boundary
on the pads this time and Guptil flicks it through square leg
good length, but it has been slid down leg again. Deflects off Guptill's thigh to long leg while he was trying a flick
goes full and pushes it across Brownlie, who slices it to deep third man
nice and tight on middle and Guptill has to check his front-foot push so that it doesn't lob to short cover
good length ball on middle, Guptill directs it to mid-on
flighted on off stump, Brownlie is forward to defend
neatly nudged off the pads. Oof, and it seems I have underestimated his timing. As has the midwicket fielder. Magnificently done from Brownlie
slides on with the arn and Brownlie is able to defend a good length ball that was threatening middle
flighted in on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
gets down the track and makes room for himself while doing so and he's threaded the gap into the covers. None of the fielders moved
third of the over? Not quite. Length and on the pads, Brownlie is just as adept off the back foot as he tucks the ball through midwicket.
full on off stump, Guptill presents the full face back at the bowler
teaser outside off and Guptill wants to flay it through cover point. Flash and miss
touch of curl back in off an appreciably fullish length, Guptill manages not to get tangled up with his footwork and clips it wide of mid-on

bounce! Edged! Taken! Terrific channel from the tall fast bowler who catches Guptill on the crease with a shortish delivery that darted across him after pitching. The batsman tried to open the face to get better control of his poke. No such luck as Shafiq dives to his right and makes no mistake

another edge! But this time Williamson is lucky enough to ride the ball past the two slips that are in place. Irfan has hit a beautiful length and his ability to extract bounce from any pitch has even the in-form batsmen in trouble
short and a shade wide of off stump, slapped into the covers
tossed up on off stump, Williamson takes care of it with a defensive bat
lures him a bit further outside off and Williamson wants to feel bat on ball as he pushes into the covers
drives a tossed up delivery on off stump back at the bowler
a little shimmy down the pitch, but Williamson can only block again
straying a touch too straight and Williamson is able to work it into the midwicket region
another little nudge from Brownlie, and this time Zulfiqar cuts across and forces the batsmen to rethink the single
back of a length and outside off, Williamson watches it safely into the keeper's gloves. Irfan clocking in the late 130 kph so far
141kph, good length ball on middle, Williamson plants the straight bat down on it
gets up off his feet, and he has to as well to punch the shortish delivery into the covers
top shot! He uses Irfan's bounce to his benefit by jumping back and cracking a shortish delivery through point. Not quite the horizontal cut. More a back-foot square drive
so Irfan bowls full and beats the New Zealand captain! Williamson brings a straight bat down inside the line as the ball goes on with the angle across him

short and wide and away it goes - to the fine leg boundary! Williamson is beaten by pace and gets an inside edge. The keeper was moving to his right, in the direction of the ball coming to him, and had no chance
flighted on middle, Brownlie unveils a pleasing on-drive but can't get it past mid-on
pushed into the covers, quite firmly as well
tapped to square leg as he stays back to a length ball that was tailing in on leg stump
stays back and tucks a flatter delivery to the right of mid-on. His timing's been good today
nimble feet gets him down to the good length ball on off stump and defends
stays back as he knew this would be a flatter delivery after the last ball and taps it to long-on
shortish and a shade outside off, defended
reaches out to try and cut a short and wide delivery, but gets it off the bottom of the bat towards point
back of a length and slid across the right-hander, Brownlie pokes and misses. Those feet don't quite move against the kind of bounce Irfan can generate
stays back, lets the back of a length delivery come on and runs it to point
another play and miss for Brownlie as this time Irfan gets the ball fuller and in the off-stump channel
a bit too much angle that time and Williamson nudges it off his pads to square leg
tossed up outside off, Williamson drives gently to the left of mid-off
plants his bat in front of bat to keep a good length ball out of his stumps
drifting down the leg side and it's been called a wide by the umpire
stays back and works the flatter delivery off leg stump wide of mid-on
worked towards the vacant midwicket region as Williamson employs soft hands and shows off supple wrists
stays back and punches a shortish delivery from off stump to mid-on
good length ball on off stump, defended
short and far too far outside off for Williamson to reach with his cut
the cross-seamer gets the inside edge in reply as Williamson looks to force the shortish ball outside off through the covers
full and outside off, Brownlie stands and delivers a drive to mid-off
good length ball on off stump, caressed to mid-off again
short and outside off, slapped into the covers

huge appeal for lbw from Anwar, but umpire Raza has walked away from his mark. Signals leg-bye and after a few looks around at the bowler and the keeper, Afridi has gone for a referral. Legitimate ball. It was short and skidded on to hit Brownlie on the back thigh. Too quick for his pull and the ball sneaked under his bat as well. Height might be the concern and HawkEye says it would have bounced over middle stump
clipped off middle stump towards deep square leg. Brownlie knows Afridi won't spin the ball, or flight it too much and has decided to camp right back in his crease
gets forward to block a good length ball on off stump
reaches to the pitch of a flighted ball and smothers it
driven past Afridi's left for an easy single to long-off
gets forward and turns the flighted ball in front of mid-on
nudges the flighted delivery from off stump to square leg
good length ball on off stump, pushed down the ground
whipped off middle stump to long leg. Lovely contact from Brownlie. He played a similar shot in the last game and got the ball through midwicket for four
good-looking drive into the off side and Afridi has to scamper across to his left to stop it at mid-off
slanted in on the pads and Williamson sneaks a couple with the long leg fielder being a touch slow. Haris Sohail was the culprit. Good glance, better running
stands up tall behind a shortish ball outside off and punches it to cover
stays back to punch a back of a length delivery past the bowler and down to mid-off
slower through the air and a bit more flight outside off, Brownlie drives carefully into the covers
that time there was some spin and Afridi has his hands on his head as Brownlie came forward, when he could have stayed back, and gets an outside edge to short third man
turned away off middle and off to deep square leg
goes on with the arm, and it skids just a touch as well to beat Williamson on the flick
beaten by flight, but Williamson has used soft hands and manage to keep the ball from lobbing up to short cover
shortish and otuside off, chopped into the covers
good length ball outside off, dabbed away in front of point
change of pace almost does Brownlie in! It's the offcutter and he closes the face too early, looking for the gap at midwicket. Gets a bit of leading edge, but it falls well short of the bowler
clipped away off middle stump to deep midwicket. New Zealand's fifty has been raised
good length ball with a hint of inward movement. Williamson tucks it to midwicket
targets the base of off stump with the offcutter, Williamson defends it
shortish on leg stump, Williamson taps it on top of the bounce through midwicket
gets down the track and drives to long-on
drags this ball short and Brownlie is unable to take advantage. Slaps it into the covers and Younis dives to his right and parries it away
good length ball, pushed to the left of Younis at cover
got too close to the pitch and jams the ball back at the bowler. He did make sure he had enough room for the shot
a touch short and he backs away to cut to deep point
good length ball, outside off, driven off the open face to the sweeper
137kph, back of a length on off stump, tapped to mid-on
outside edge, but it doesn't carry! It's the slower ball from Anwar and it was very drivable. Brownlie is sucked into the trap and is lucky it doesn't reach the wicketkeeper
short and a shade wide of off stump, cracked to point
full on off stump, whirling wrists come into play as he whips the ball through midwicket
back of a length and cutting in at him, Williamson lets it come on and runs it to point

whoa! Take a bow, Kane W! It was full on off stump and he planted his front foot beside it and merely extended his defence. Mike Hesson used "destructive" to describe the NZ captain, there was evidence of it
shortish on off stump, chopped into the covers
glorious strike! The part-timer spinner should not be allowed to settle and Brownlie has come down the track, made some room and lifted the ball over extra cover.
turns a good length ball away through midwicket
a skip down the track gets him to the pitch of the flighted ball outside off, driven to the left of mid-off
shortish and outside off, Williamson backs away and cuts to the sweeper
tapped down to mid-on to retain strike
opens the face as he stays beside a short ball outside off to deep point. That's the fifty partnership
slower ball on middle, but Williamson has spotted it and countered it with a strong roll of his wrists. Skims away to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, Williamson nudges towards point
angled in on middle and leg, and it slides off Williamson's pads to the keeper
brilliant batting. Jumped inside the line, got on top of the short ball and rolled his wrists to send the ball scurrying to the long leg boundary. Too quick for Babar down there
good length, punched into the covers
gets down the track, to the pitch of the ball and drives to long-off
Goes back to a good length ball and pushes past the bowler's right
Looped up on off stump to tempt Brownlie into a slog sweep. Mistimes it to deep square leg. Think that ball dipped
Flatter ball on off stump, pushed back down the pitch
Slices the length ball towards the covers
Gets down the track and lifts the flighted delivery on middle stump to deep cover. He's extremely good with that stroke. Time for drinks
sits up with you bowl short on this pitch and Brownlie has thumped it to deep point
flatter delivery on middle, punched to long-on
gets down the track, turns a flighted delivery into a full toss and drives to long-off
goes a touch wide of the crease with a tossed up ball on off stump, Kane W blocks
he's able to get into such good positions to pick the gap. This was tossed up on leg stump, but he had leaned forward, made room simultaneously and drills the ball to deep point
down the track, but this would have been a full toss even if he had waited. Bunted to long-off

up comes the finger and Brownlie has missed out on a start again! Had a chat with his captain and then decides to walk off. It was too plumb to even hope. Plays down the wrong line to a fuller delivery that slides on with the arm. Hit very low on the pads and quite adjacent with the stumps
flighted on leg stump, defended
good length ball on off stump, blocked again
turned away to deep square leg to get off the mark. Tossed up, but angled a bit too far in
good length ball skids on to Williamson who has to hurry into pushing it down to long-off

huge appeal from the keeper, but Zulfiqar knew this was sliding down leg. His pace is just quick enough to cause the batsman to be late on his shot. Especially if he is playing around the front pad like Taylor was that time
too much loop on this one and Kane W belts the full toss to deep cover
flighted on off stump, driven calmly to deep cover

a shade short and Williamson has jumped back and cuts so wonderfully late. Anwar is the man sweeping on the boundary, but as hard as he runs, dives full length and parries the ball, it reaches the boundary
low full toss outside off, directed to long-on
drilled through the covers, but there is protection there
flighted on middle, Williamson nudges to long-on and has to settle for a single
tossed up and dipping on off stump, Williamson is happy to block
stays back and clips a good length ball to deep midwicket
covers the line of a flatter delivery on middle and keeps it out
pushed through on off stump, Taylor taps it towards long-on, waits to see if midwicket can cut across and then sets off after he couldn't
inside edge onto pad as Zulfiqar's pace off the pitch stymies Williamson
driven to long-off and he raises yet another one-day fifty. His eighth in 10 matches, and he converted the last one into a match-winning ton
stays back and works a length ball to long-on
tossed up on off stump, defended
slices the flatter delivery outside off in front of point and collects a couple of runs
tossed up on off stump, Taylor pushes the ball through the covers
goes back and punches the good length ball down to long-on to raise his 2000th ODI run, the youngest NZ player to that mark
flighted on off stump, defended towards the covers
looped up outside off and Williamson takes it on the full to long-off
tucks the good length ball through midwicket
driven back at the bowler as Williamson gets too close to the pitch of the ball outside off
makes him reach out to a tossed up ball outside off, driven uppishly past the bowler
flighted on off stump, defended
slid down the leg side, Taylor cannot connect with his leg glance
tossed up outside off, driven smoothly to deep cover
falls a yard or so short of a diving Akmal! Taylor had committed to a drive too early, the good length ball holds on the pitch and makes it spoon into the covers
a touch shortish and outside off, slid to short third man where Irfan does some good work
length on off stump, pushed down to mid-off
leans forward and drives the flighted ball to mid-off again
oooh, that was close as well. Williamson closed the face early and the flighted delivery, grips into the pitch and lures the leading edge. But it doesn't carry to the bowler
driven solidly to long-off this time
good length ball on off stump, defended
stays tall behind the flatter ball and punches it to long-on
a touch of turn outside off and Taylor gets an outside edge on his forward defensive. Finds point
flighted on middle and leg, turned to square leg
flighted on off stump, pushed to long-off
flighted on leg stump, turned behind square leg
taps the flatter delivery towards cover
opens the face in an attempt to run a fuller delivery behind point, but Shehzad is quite alert there
slanted in on middle and leg to make Taylor play with a closed face, searching for the gap at midwicket, gets a leading edge down the pitch
tossed up on leg stump, swept gently to short fine leg
goes back and punches a flatter delivery to long-off
shovels a well flighted delivery on leg stump to long-off. Managed to make room rather well there
tossed up on middle, Taylor pushes the ball to long-on
skids on a shade outside off, Williamson is able to run it to short third man. Checked his stroke at the last minute there and played with a much straighter bat
flighted on off stump, Williamson drives through a diving Pakistan fielder to long-on
flighted in on middle, defended towards mid-off
leans forward and pushes in front of point and they set off immediately to collect a quick single
flat and quick on leg stump, tucked away through midwicket
pushed into the straight midwicket region and the bowler himself has to chase after it
tossed up on leg stump, pushed down to long-on
stays back and cuts the shortish ball outside off to point
leans over the flighted ball on leg stump and turns it wide of long-on. Couple taken
short and wide, goes for the cut, but he can't connect and is quite disappointed with that.
good length ball on off stump, forced past the bowler's left
flighted on off stump, defended carefully
good length ball that keeps a tad low on off stump, Williamson is hardly troubled as he blocks on the front foot
short and wide, Williamson chops it to deep cover
flighted on off stump, defended
slid down the leg side and Taylor works it in front of square leg
opens the face and slides a fuller delivery on off stump towards the covers
tossed up on middle and leg, Taylor works with the angle and whips to long-on
good length ball outside off, Williamson looks to slap it into the off side but fails to connect
flighted on off stump, driven to long-on
flighted on middle, turns the ball through to deep midwicket
a shade short and wide, Williamson reaches for it and gets a thick outside edge to short third man
good length ball on off stump, defended down the pitch
shortish on off stump, Taylor dabs it between point and cover and picks up a well-earned single
short and wide outside off, Williamson cuts to deep point
chops the ball behind point, not much room to work with but it was short. There's the second successive fifty partnership today for New Zealand
good length ball on off stump, defended with soft hands to point
offcutter outside off, punched to mid-off
can't pierce the field behind point even as he went back to cut the short ball outside off
tossed up on middle, driven to long-off

that's a KW special! Runs at the spinner and lifts him over extra cover and it is so very clean! Didn't quite reach the pitch, but he goes through with the stroke and timed it to perfection because of the amount of room he made for himself
driven into the gap in the covers again
chops the ball into the covers
gets forward and drives the flighted ball on off stump to mid-off. Shehzad fumbles
lets the shortish ball come on outside off and carves it to deep third man
full-length offcutter which has been tapped down to long-on
plays with an open stance against seam bowling as well and drives the fuller ball outside off to deep cover
good length ball on middle, clipped from the crease to long-on
is that his first boundary? Yep! It was full and sliding down leg and Taylor persuades it to run away to the long leg boundary. Irfan was the fielder there, and he tends to be sluggish
shortish and outside off, Taylor gets back and across to slice the ball to third man
back of a length on off stump, can only defend
good length ball pushed across the right-hander, Taylor shoulders arms
back of a length and outside off, not bothered with
shortish and outside off, slapped away to deep point
beaten outside off! Irfan persists with his probing line just outside off and finally Taylor has been tempted into playing
full and outside off, driven through the covers
works the angle to his favour as he glances the good length ball to short fine leg
good length on middle and leg, but Williamson uses his feet to get to the pitch and lofts it over extra cover again. I daresay he can play that stroke in his sleep
angled in too far down leg and Williamson has jumped across outside off and sweeps to the long leg boundary. Toying with the spinner now
stands up tall behind the flatter ball on off stump and pushes to extra cover
pushed through on middle and leg, Williamson nudges it to long-on
tapped towards midwicket, which is vacant so there is an easy single on offer
shortish and outside off, Taylor pokes and gets a thick outside edge to deep third man
fuller ball outside off, Williamson gets back and across and slides it down to third man

but he should have been at orthodox first slip for that to be a chance! The angle across the right-hander works for Irfan as Taylor defends tentatively. A healthy outside edge is taken, but it flies past the keeper's right
full and wide outside off, Taylor does not bother with it
short and a shade wide of off stump, but that's Taylor's staple as he cuts to deep point
goes across outside off to tuck a good length ball into the midwicket region. Time for drinks
pushed back at the bowler
gets down the pitch and turns the good length ball outside leg to deep midwicket
flighted on off stump, driven back at the bowler
short and wide, Taylor cuts to point
flighted on leg stump, pushed to long-on
slider from Afridi has Williamson in some trouble. Struck on the pads with him waiting for spin. Afridi appeals, but the umpire says it would have slid down leg. Pakistan have no reviews
back of a length and wide outside off, Taylor is not keep on it
taps the shortish ball outside off towards point
lovely push to mid-off and he was almost ready to run with the shot before realising he had timed the ball too well to pinch a run
shortish on leg stump, tucked away to deep square leg
good length ball on off stump, defended at the bowler
that gully isn't doing much help as Williamson is quite happy to wait for a shortish delivery to and use the open face to find deep third man

likes the fuller length as Taylor taps it down the ground and reaches fifty in pleasing fashion. It's not been his best innings, but it has had a lot of purpose. New Zealand have the platform now. Do they have the fuel down the order to blast off from it?
good length ball outside off, punched to long-off
stays back to a flatter ball on off stump and Taylor tucks it through the vacant midwicket region. Zulfiqar has to race after it himself and keeps it to a single
gets down the track and has mistimed a chip over mid-on. Gets quite a lot of height on it and must have had a few flutters as Umar Akmal back-pedalled after it. Just about lobs him
flighted on off stump, swiped to deep midwicket
stays in the crease against a flat delivery on middle and turns it through midwicket
shortish and outside off, Williamson waits but should have waited just a bit more. Mistimes a pull to long-on
looped in on off stump, defended
turned through midwicket as he stepped forward to a fuller ball on middle
a touch short on off stump, Williamson stands up behind it and pushes to long-off
tossed up on off stump, driven to extra cover
skips down the track and pushes the good length ball to long-on
good length ball outside off, defended for a quick single into the covers
back of a length on off stump, tucked towards midwicket. Been a profitable region
backs away to a short ball outside off and claps it wide of mid-off
full and wide outside off, but Taylor doesn't bother as he swipes the ball very hard and ends up mistiming it to long-on
KW was moving outside leg, Anwar followed him with a full delivery which is whipped to deep square leg. Does he even know he is in the nervous nineties?
full on middle, Taylor was reaching forward to lap-sweep the ball. Just about connects, otherwise he might well have been plumb. Single to long leg then
slower delivery, quite wide of off stump. Williamson waits on it and slaps it off the bottom of the bat to deep point. Retains strike on 97

he's walking! The sweep, and the need to score quickly, has ended a magnificent innings from the New Zealand captain. Tossed up a lot slower than the other Afridi darts which makes the top-edge appear, deflect off the peak of his helmet, I think and then sit in the gloves of the wicketkeeper who was running forward
quicker and flatter on off stump, Ronch manages to slice it towards point

goes for a cut and the inside edge rolls onto his back boot. Lo and behold, once the new batsman is in the pitch and the bowling plays tricks. Not to mention a roaring Abu Dhabi crowd is firmly behind Pakistan

ooh! What a delivery from Afridi! It was a good length ball and drifts in alarmingly at Taylor. The pace he is getting off this pitch is stunning. Ample gap between bat and pad and an inside edge saves him from getting bowled. The umpire though has not spotted it. Taylor did have a quick question with umpire Raza about that as he completed three runs
fuller delivery skids on quite sharply again and has Ronchi playing across the line and quite late at that
short and wide, Taylor cuts strongly to deep point
good length ball ties him down on off stump
backs away to a fuller delivery on leg stump and drills it back at the bowler
fuller ball, it was the offcutter, Taylor spots it as he walks at the bowler and slogs it away to deep square leg. That's a very productive T20 stroke for him
picks it up off a length from outside off and lifts it to deep square leg

that's huuuuuge! Anwar fails the final overs test as he offers an overpitched delivery that Taylor has stepped forward to and carted away over long-on. There was a man there, but he backed himself to clear him
shortish and down the leg side, Ronchi was hoping to swat it away but it was too far to connect
short and wide outside off, Ronchi has jumped back and flat-batted it to the straight boundary. He likes pace on the ball and he's showing that off
shortish and outside off, Ronchi has found his timing now as he carves it to deep point. Skimmed off the open face
Taylor though continues to struggle against Irfan as a short and wide delivery beats his cut
looks to blast the length ball from where he stood, but watches it sail past his flashing blade and onto the keeper's gloves
fuller ball on off stump, pushed to mid-off and gets a single
clears that front leg and uses the room on this shortish ball to thump it to deep point
flat and a shade outside off, Ronchi slices it to point
the need to bowl flat and fast is hurting his ability to land the ball. This is a full toss Taylor leans forward and swipes it away to the square leg boundary
a touch slower outside off and Taylor misses with his slog catch
this is a top edge, but falls safe from the man at deep square leg. Got under the ball a bit too much, but those shots need to be played now
pushed through on middle, Taylor jumped across to try and sweep the ball to long leg but is struck on the pads
full and on leg stump, Taylor moved outside off and slogs the ball behind square leg. He is extremely proficient with that mow

back of a length on leg stump, Ronchi has launched it over the long-on boundary! How did he play that off the front foot, and how did he time it so well? Extra bounce from Irfan, Ronchi says thank you very much

runs down the track and he's toe-ended it! Afridi lines it up, but it pops out! Juggles it once, then again, and finally pouches it with his left hand behind him. Good composure from the Pakistan captain and Ronchi's breezy little knock ends
fuller ball outside off, pushed through the covers
short and wide outside off, Latham caresses it to point
full and tailing in at Latham, who musters an inside edge to long leg
shortish on off stump, dabbed in front of point for a single
backs away against a slider and has to hurry into tapping the ball towards point
how's that for a reply! Gets down the track, made some room and emulated his captain's lift over extra cover. Magnificent strike
goes for a sweep to a good length ball, misses it. Keeper asks for a stumping, not given
comes down the track and chips a flat and fast delivery to long-on
gets beside the almost yorker length delivery and slices it through point

walks at the bowler, but Zulfiqar shortens his length and reduces his pace. Nudged to deep square leg and Taylor captures two runs. Beautiful cricket. Batsman tried to outwit the bowler, but the bowler was wise to it, and the batsman said he was good enough to profit despite it all.
gets down the track and ends up turning a fuller ball into a yorker wide outside off, sliced to point
right up there on off stump, Latham can only dig it out
banged in short in reply to the batsman stepping down at him. Latham instinctively sways away
short and wide, Latham has slugged it to the wide long-on boundary. Stepped forward and unleashed a full swing of his arms
offers a clean view of his stumps as he looks for a lap sweep with fine leg up in the ring, but the fuller ball is too quick for him. Beaten outside off
poor ball and Latham has walloped a full toss to the midwicket boundary. Mixed over that, and it's cost eight
targets the base of middle stump, but Taylor has managed to whip it past short fine leg to collect a couple of runs
full on middle, Taylor swipes it behind square leg but can't beat the fielder on the boundary. Gee, those wrists of his are powerful
slower short ball, Taylor pulls to deep midwicket and he has to relinquish strike. That hundred looks a lot further away now
picks the offcutter on leg stump and heaves it away to long leg
another offcutter, on a length which helps Latham out as he swings his arms across the line and connects strongly. That's the sort of shots you play in this situation
finds a yorker just outside off, Latham inside edges it to deep midwicket and New Zealand have 275

inn2.comm: late curl in at Jamshed whose feet aren't quite ready to move yet. Pushes to mid-on
131kph, opens the face and slices the shortish ball outside off to point
back of a length and outside off, Jamshed is behind it with a drill to mid-off
139kph, fuller on off stump, Jamshed blocks it back at the bowler

given out leg before, but Jamshed is wondering if it was pitched outside leg. Has a loooong conversation with his partner and loses the time that was there to opt for a review. New Zealand have been hustling batsmen out with pace all through the series and this one was just on a good length and skids onto the batsman. Brings out the panicked swipe across the line and is struck in line with off stump. Clearly pitched outside leg, oh dear, umpire Wilson...
139kph, good length ball outside off, Younis is unsure whether to play or leave and ends up dabbing the ball to the slips
back of a length on middle and leg, Shehzad is jumpy as he blocks to mid-on
145kph, this good length ball strays a bit too far outside off, left well alone
144kph, full on off stump, Shehzad pushes it to mid-on
146kph, outside edge squirts away to deep third man. Shehzad was a bit squared up as he blocks a good length awayswinger
bouncer sent down a shade outside off. Shehzad sways away from the line and comes down to do a bit of gardening
150.6 kph, doesn't need too many balls to break that mark, does he? fuller on and around off stump, Shehzad looks to drive into the covers and is slow on it. Toe ended to the fielder
kept the ball quite full and it curled in at Younis, who uses it to clip the ball through midwicket
137kph, caught on the crease as he defends a good length ball off the back foot. Might have come forward there
137kph, back of a length and outside off, cautiously left alone
taps it into the off side with soft hands, absorbs all the pace on this back of a length delivery, and gets a single into the covers
full on off stump, pushed down the pitch with a very straight bat
back of a length on middle and leg, looks for a flick but wears it on the thigh
150.5 kph, hangs his bat outside off and edges it down to the man at second slip. The pace is fine, but making sure the batsman plays at it is Milne's greatest strength

150kph, drilled between point and cover for a couple, oh wait, Shehzad wants three and he gets it! Brilliant work from the opener. First in getting into position to power the stroke into the gap and then to judge the extra run
full on off stump, defended into the off side
tests the middle of the pitch at 148 kph, Younis sees it outside off and sways away
144kph, a touch fuller outside off and it curls away quite sharply after Younis lets it pass. Ronchi is nicely behind it though
144kph, full on off stump, nicely driven to mid-off
good length ball outside off, pushed to mid-off
144kph, jumps inside the line of a shortish ball on middle and leg and clips it to long leg
137kph, bouncer right at the badge! Goes for a hook on instinct and barely manages to evade the keeper running to his left
shortish on off stump, Shehzad gets behind it and blocks with soft hands
good length ball on off stump, defended solidly
good length ball on off stump, keeps it out
phew! That was a scorching yorker! That high backlift manage to get down in time to keep the inswinger from rattling his stumps
clipped with the swing to deep square leg. Lovely work with the wrists from Younis
gets inside the line of a good length ball on leg stump and taps it into the leg side
invites the drive and Shehzad is up for the challenge. Times it perfectly but finds the man at cover
width on offer and Shehzad nails another cover drive, but can't get past Nathan McCullum
fuller and a shade outside off, Shehzad drives at mid-off
good length ball on off stump, defended if a little nervously
thinks about an appeal after a sharp inswinger thuds unto Younis' pads while he tries a flick. But there was an inside edge involved
back of a length and outside off, Younis opens the face in front of point but McCullum there is too quick. Denies the single
low full toss outside off, pushed at mid-off
jumps across on off stump to block a shortish delivery on off stump
full and sliding down leg, whipped to long leg
top bouncer from Mitch Mc. There must be something in the name! Banged in on middle and forces Younis to leap off his feet, soften his hands and drop it by his feet. Well done in the end
full on off stump, drummed into the off side where Brownlie dives to his right from short cover and keeps it to a single
full on leg stump, clipped past short midwicket but mid-on mops up
that had looked like the first boundary until the speedy Milne raced to his right and pulled out a full-length dive at mid-on. A touch overpitched and Shehzad had timed his push quite well
another bouncer, New Zealand definitely seem to be working Younis over, and he knows it as he ducks under the ball
back of a length delivery pushed across the right-hander keeps quite low. Younis is beaten, but no one would blame him
banged in short and Shehzad is happy to sink below it
dug in short and Shehzad has pulled it to deep square leg
full on middle and off, and the bit of awayswing opens Younis up. Gets a leading edge that lobs over short cover
back of a length on off stump, Younis taps it to mid-on and sets off. Well done

strangled down the leg side! It's the short ball that does him again, and he goes after it. He might have imagined a deft little glance to long leg for perhaps a boundary, but ends up gloving to the keeper
cuts back in off a shortish length and nails him on the thigh pad. Shafiq is caught in the crease as he tries to flick
fuller ball on off stump, defended
good length ball on off stump, pushed down to mid-off for a quick single
oof, Shafiq is lured into driving on the up against a good length ball that straightens outside off. Soundly beaten
fuller on off stump, turned past a diving short midwicket towards mid-on
shortish and outside off, sliced to point
good length ball outside off, not bothered with
flighted in on off stump, driven to long-off
seeks the blockhole on off stump, Shafiq jams it back to long-off
offers up a full toss on leg stump and Shehzad has swept it for the first boundary of the innings. Abu Dhabi, of course, roars

flatter delivery goes on with the arm and strikes him on the pads! Looks so very close, but the umpire disagrees. Kane W says lets get on with it. There was a lot going for this shout. The batsman was playing outside the line, he was late on it as well and he was struck on the back pad. I don't think there had been an inside edge either
goes wide of the crease and gets the slider to stay low! Gets an inside edge and it wanders away past the leg stump
good length ball on off stump, defended tentatively
flighted outside off, driven at short cover
brings the batsman forward and Shafiq drives to mid-off
short and wide outside off, slapped away to deep point
flighted outside off, he gets inside the line and drives to the left of mid-off
flatter ball on off stump, punched down to long-on
eased into the covers for a single
gets down the track, reaches the ball on the full and whips it to deep midwicket
lunges forward and turns a good length ball through square leg
gets forward and forces a good length ball into the covers
comes down the track, but Devcich pulls his length back and forces Shafiq to tap to mdiwicket

this time the finger comes up from umpire Wilson. Shafiq walks up to check with Shehzad and then goes for a review. Another arm ball on middle and off stump and it tempted the batsman to play around the front pad. This looks out, struck in front of off stump and would go on to clip leg stump. Umpire's call will be upheld
stays around to the left-hander and the flighted delivery to nudged towards midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
around the wicket to the left-hander. This is a touch short and wide and it holds into the pitch as well. Sohail reaches with his hands and pushes it to long-off
flatter delivery sliding down, Shehzad goes for a sweep and it is cut short at short fine leg by Devcich
backs away and taps a length ball down to long-off
slower through the air this time and its been pushed down to long-on
good length on off stump, Shehzad rolls his wrists on it and taps it back to the bowler
good length ball on middle, clipped to deep square leg and three men crowd around the ball, which means even though there was a minor fumble, it costs only one
tossed up on off stump, soft hands allows Shehzad a single into the covers
nudged wide of long-on as Sohail gets to the pitch of a flighted delivery on off stump
flat and outside off, slapped to the sweeper
nudged off the pads as Devich tries to limit the room he gives the batsman
gets down the track and Shehzad was blocking down the wrong line. Struck on the pad, a shade outside off too perhaps. Devcich though is keen to appeal, while the batsmen grab a single
tossed up outside off, pushed into the off side
driven  down to long-on as he reaches to the pitch with a good front foot stride
flighted in on middle, driven to long-on to bring up Pakistan's fifty
short and wide outside off, Shehzad was loading up for a big slash over the off side and mistimes it. Pitch is slowing up a lot now
flighted on off stump, punched down to long-on
flighted on off stump, defended

brilliant work from Guptill as he throws himself to his right, leaps back up and forces Shehzad to dive back in his crease. The drive was well-struck, so much that the batsman had decided there was a clear single on offer. In the end, he would have been out had it been a direct hit
short and wide outside off, Shehzad slaps it to Guptill, who misfields and allows a quick single this time
backs away to try and create some room, but Devcich lobs the ball outside off and beyond his reach
flighted on middle and leg, driven to long-on
gets down the track and pushes the ball back to the bowler. Devcich gets around to it and collides with the non-striker
slider on middle and off, Shehzad backs away to cut and nails it. But finds point
shortish and outside off, Sohail guides it behind point to get off strike
144kph, fuller delivery outside off gets a thick outside edge to deep third man
146kph, stays in line with a shortish delivery on off stump and slices it to point
144kph, beautiful stroke from Sohail. He isn't in the least bit ruffled by Milne's pace as he punches the back of a length ball in front of point this time
goes for a pull, but a 149 kph delivery is not so easy to get away. Thuds into his bat when he was only halfway through the stroke and it goes to mid-on
149kph, stands and delivers a drive to deep cover and that will be drinks
big dive from Devcich keeps it to three. It was a quicker, flatter delivery on the pads and Shehzad glances it quite fine
rocks back to punch a shortish ball to long-off
goes back to a good length ball on middle and works it through square leg. Good work
a bit of turn as the ball holds in the pitch and nearly fooled Sohail. The back-foot block nearly carried back to the bowler
slipped down the leg side, but the umpire has not called it a wide
goes back and drills a flatter delivery to long-on
149 kph and this back of a length delivery straightens away from the angle. Sohail is caught in the crease while attempting a block. Well beaten

short and a shade outside off, Shehzad goes for a pull and manages to lob it over mid-on. Devcich sets off after it like he has rocket-powered roller skates. And an off-balance throw keeps it to two, and then he cushions his fall with his hands
opens the face and slices the ball into the covers
152.8kph, fuller delivery on off stump, pushed down the ground
directs a bouncer on middle and Sohail ducks under it
another searing bouncer at 150 kph and Sohail has to leap off his feet and dab the ball towards point. Good composure from the batsman

you just can't get easy runs with this New Zealand fielding. There was some width on offer and Shehzad has sliced the ball quite well behind point. Only Brownlie hurtles after it, slides and flicks the ball back
turned away through midwicket
flighted outside off, dabbed in front of point for a single
pulls his length just a bit back, Sohail who was on the front foot has to adjust with his hands
reaches forward to defend a tossed up delivery back at the bowler
looped up outside off, Shehzad goes for a sweep and is struck on the pads. Outside the line though and they take a single into the covers
tossed up on off stump, ends up a low full toss, Sohail taps it to midwicket
gets this away straighter and the clip goes down to long-on
good length ball outside off, Shehzad looks to slice it behind point where Mitch Mc dives and palms the ball to point
N Mac this time dives to his right at midwicket and refuses the single off a backfoot push
punched to long-on
tossed up on leg stump, clipped over the midwicket region for a single
flighted on off stump, fluently driven to long-off
goes back and slices a shortish delivery towards short third man, Adam Milne misfields to his right. Slips on the turf, possibly some dew
Devich! leaps away to his left to cut a push down the ground in its tracks
shrotish ball on middle, tucked to midwicket
backs away and taps a flatter ball on middle towards the covers
good length ball on off stump, defended towards short midwicket
gets down the track and nudges to short midwicket again
backs away to try and pull, but the ball skids onto him too quickly and he has to adjust. Punched to long-on instead
chipped toward short midwicket, but it falls short of the man. Use of the feet doesn't give him profit that time
goes back and pushes a shortish delivery down to long-off
flighted on middle, Shehzad turns it to long-on and takes a single
flighted outside off, slapped into the covers off the front foot
down the track, but gets too close to the good length ball. Ends up digging it out back to the bowler

was there an inside edge? Yep, Ronchi has dropped an immensely tough take. Shehzad went for a sweep off a good length ball outside off, gets a tiny little deflection that the keeper cannot convert. Too hard, was a reflex catch
flighted on middle, defended
flatter on middle, punched to long-on
good length ball on middle, defended back at the bowler
pushed through on off stump, Shehzad turns it past a diving short midwicket to long-on.
only the second boundary of the innings, and it was a super one too. Lovely use of the feet and a clean, correct cricket shot against a good length ball outside off
shortish on middle and leg, pushed down to long-on
jumps down the track, but McCullum doesn't give him the length to take advantage. Defended
advances on the bowler and pushes the ball towards long-on
two in the over! Shehzad jumps back against a short ball, makes some room for himself and cuts strongly behind point
gets a thick edge and the shortish ball outside off runs down to deep third man

second outside edge in as many balls and this short and wide delivery flies down towards the third man boundary. And again there was another flying New Zealand fielder, Dean Brownlie, stopping the boundary. Fifty for Shehzad, needs to convert though
shortish on off stump, worked away off the back foot through midwicket
back of a length on off stump, it was the offcutter and the batsman has punched it back at the bowler. Henry feigned a throw and Sohail stands his ground and gestures at the bowler to calm down
full on off stump, pushed down to mid-on
too close to cut and he is beaten. Just back of a length and around fifth stump, could have played a punch through the covers perhaps
tossed up and drifting in on middle, Shehzad drives to long-on
goes around the stumps and delivers a good length ball that pitches and turns before Sohail can reach it. Gets an thick outside edge to point
down the track and drilled to long-on to raise the Pakistan hundred
driven to extra cover as Shehzad uses his feet to get to the pitch of a flighted ball outside off
pushed to long-on as Shehzad gets his dancing shoes on against a flatter delivery as well
heaved away over long-on! Chose the right ball to come down to and a clean swing of the arms sends the ball sailing over the fielder
Catching practice! Chooses to force a back of a length delivery off the front foot and possibly chip it over mid-on. Ends up gifting that fielder, Kane W, the simplest of catches
shortish and outside off, dabbed towards point
gets behind a shortish ball on off stump, defended

oh dear! That looks awful! Devcich has landed on his right shoulder and seems to have hurt it very badly. I think it has popped out! It was a length ball and Akmal loaded up for a slap down the ground and has toe-ended it. Devcich rushes to his left from mid-off and dives forward to try and catch it and he does, but the ball pops out as he hit the turf. He's walked off the field now
back of a length and outside off, punched into the covers
shortish on middle and leg, Sohail has swatted it through wide mid-on. Powerful stroke
fuller ball on off stump, pushed down towards mid-off but short cover gets to it first
good length ball outside off, driven smartly through the covers for a couple. Lovely timing
another good-looking drive off a fuller ball that was directed across him. Short cover is beaten on his left
good length ball on middle and leg, defended
back of a length on off stump, defended towards point
shortish and cramping him on middle, Akmal tries a flick and gets it off the leading edge. Goes too far wide of backward point
good length ball on off stump, defended
defends the good length arm ball on off stump.
you beauty, Martin Guptill. It was a rank long hop from N Mac and Akmal had jumped back for a blistering pull. Only he fails to keep it down, and forgets about placement. Picks out short midwicket
flighted outside off, driven to long-on
flighted on off stump, driven back at the bowler
goes back and clips a flatter delivery behind square leg
hits the shoulder with the short ball. Sohail has taken his eye off it while taking cover. If your name's Mitch, you're the enforcer
moves around the wicket and probes a full length on leg stump. Sohail backs away and slices towards mid-off
looks to back away again and Mitch one-ups him by sliding the ball wide outside off and beyond his reach
attempts a slower bouncer on middle and leg, Sohail manages to hook it down to long leg
shortish and outside off, Sarfraz, the new batsman, punches it through point
nails a yorker on middle, Sohail jams his bat down on it and secures a single to mid-on
flighted on leg stump, makes room and drives to long-on
down the track and lifts the ball over short midwicket. Strong bottom hand gives him all the power he needs to grab a boundary
flatter delivery on middle and off, defended
good length ball on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
brings down a straight bat on a fuller delivery on off stump to long-on
slider on middle and leg, Sohail gets it off the inside part of the bat to long-on
flighted outside off from around the wicket, Sohail drives at cover
comes down the track to a length ball and pushes it down to long-on
flatter on off stump, Sarfraz pulls out the old faithful sweep for a single to deep square leg
shortish and outside off, Sohail had committed to the front foot and pushes the ball to long-off
quicker and flatter, Sarfraz backs away to cut and gets an inside edge that squirts away in front of sort fine leg
down the track to flat delivery and pushes through the covers
advances down the pitch and drives a good length ball to long-off
hop, skip and jump down the track to find long-on off a flatter delivery on off stump
backs away against a slower delivery outside off and cuts to deep cover
flighted outside off to tempt the cover drive from Sarfraz, gets an inside edge down the pitch
flighted on off stump, driven to the right of a diving McCullum
that's the arm ball, and Sohail has managed to cut it from leg stump with an open face
back of a length and angled in on middle from around the wicket, clipped to deep midwicket
149kph, banged in short and Sohail barely manages to nudge the ball off his chest behind square leg
147kph, shortish and outside off, Sarfraz runs it down to deep third man
shortish and outside off, seemed a touch slower than his normal deliveries. And yes it was the offcutter. Sohail slaps it through to the sweeper to raise his second fifty of the series
angles the short ball in on middle stump, Sarfraz steers it to a floating slip
another short ball at the stumps and Sarfraz has jumped back to pull. Finds deep midwicket
starts with a short ball and Sarfraz is ready with the pull a touch too early. Adjusts mid-stroke and gets a single through midwicket
backs away to try and manufacture room with Mitch going around. The bowler followed him with a full ball and it's been flicked to deep midwicket
tries to make room outside leg again, Mitch follows him again with a short ball. But this time the Sohail has been able to pull it to the long leg boundary

finds a perfect yorker on leg stump, Sohail had given the bowler a clear view of the stumps and just about manages to get his bat down in time. The ball dribbles back behind the stumps and Mitch runs up after it and dives headlong after the ball to try and prevent the single. Not possible
full on middle and leg, whipped away to deep square leg. Excellent running from Sarfraz again
goes for a bouncer on off stump, Sarfraz runs it to deep third man. Might be drinks
banged in short, but Sarfraz loves it. Rocks back and nails a pull shot to the square leg boundary. Whistled away. What power!
attempts a sweep off the fastest bowler in the match delivering at 152 kph, it was outside off though. Premeditated effort does not pan out
slower ball outside off, Sarfraz cuts to point but before he got to it, cover dives to his left and stops it himself
belted down the ground! Sohail backed away to a 147 kph short ball and slapped it back over the bowler's head
tries to drum the slower ball down to long-on, but Milne dives to his left, stops it one-handed and even manages to fling down a throw to keep Sarfraz honest at the other end
full and barely a shade outside off, Sohail cleared that front leg and swung free. Soundly beaten
another slower ball that is worked away to deep midwicket, which is Chirag Suri, who misfields and gives a second run
change of pace again, Sarfraz is wise to it as he clips it to long leg
moves miles outside leg with Mitch Mc bowling around the wicket, he's waiting beyond the wide marker and drills a fuller ball to the long-off boundary

too much room on that occasion and he misses his slice! He stands there for ages, slumped over his bat after McClenaghan nails it full on off stump and roars after hitting his target. The third umpire checks on the front foot, that's okay. The back foot too for good measure. All fine. Off walks Sohail
full toss on leg stump has been clipped to long leg
slower and shortish on leg stump, nudged to long leg.

strikes first ball back in does Henry! He preempted Sarfraz making room for himself and bowled a good length delivery a little further outside off. The batsman has to play at it, there's too many runs left to get, and nicks off. Lovely, low catch from Ronchi as well
full on off stump, Anwar protects it
full on off stump, pushed back at the bowler and Henry sees the batsman out of his crease and looks for an incredible run-out. Hits the batsman instead. Apologies straight away
good length ball on off stump, defended
shortish on middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket
slower bouncer from Henry, beats Afridi who was on the pull too soon
short of a length on off stump, defended
goes short on middle, brilliant accuracy, and forces Anwar to use soft hands to block it down the pitch
slams an overpitched slower delivery to the long-off boundary. Pakistan are certainly not giving up. Target under 100 now
full on leg stump, clipped into the midwicket region for a quick single
goes around the wicket and delivers a slower ball on middle and leg, Afridi moves outside leg and steers the ball to deep third man, who had been moved finer before that ball
good length ball on middle and leg, turned away through midwicket
keeps to his crease against a fuller ball and turns it through square leg
catch, they yell. But it falls short of Guptill at long-on. Tries to stymie Afridi for room, but he still goes for the boom down the ground
fuller delivery outside leg, but Anwar leaped down the track and made room for himself to carve the ball over point. Phew, brilliant stroke
tucked away through square leg and they've raced across for a couple. The throw comes at Afridi's end and he makes it easily
what power from Anwar! Great footwork to get himself beside the ball, which was way down leg in the first place, and then lets his wrists go mad

oh, N Mac enjoyed that! The batsman was charging down the pitch again, but this time the fuller delivery was slid through quicker and wider outside off. Anwar cannot reach, and he can't get back to safety either. Top work from Ronchi
124kph, bludgeons a slower short ball to the wide long-on boundary
another slower bouncer, which Afridi allows to pass past his chest to the keeper

this is off the splice as he tries to pull a short ball on middle and leg. N Mac was hunting it down over his shoulder, threw himself at the ball, but it beats his outstretched hands. Landed on his right knee quite hard
banged in way too short at 140 kph, Afridi knows that's a wide.
outside edge flies away to deep third man. It was full on the base of off stump, Afridi unveils a slog and gets lucky

good length, back of the hand slower ball has been carted to deep midwicket and Henry has a maiden five-wicket haul in ODIs, and he's only played six matches. The crowd has begun departing, almost the second the catch was taken.
back of a length and outside off, Irfan offers a nothing poke and is beaten
full and a shade outside off, the batsman backs away to slide the ball and misses
full on middle and off, Zulfiqar slashes it through the covers

timber! New Zealand take the series in emphatic fasion! It was full, it was straight, it had Zulfiqar jumping outside the line and swinging from the hips. He misses, Milne hits and smiles all-round in the New Zealand dressing room
